chunks.markdown: REASURY *Attach Additional Sheets Here* *Read Carefully Instructions for Preparation of Invoice* (THIS FORM DOES NOT REQUIRE CERTIFICATION BY A UNITED STATES CONSULAR OFFICER)
SPECIAL CUSTOMS INVOICE U.S. CUSTOMS SERVICE (Original only required for customs purposes)

I. THIS SECTION TO BE FILLED IN FOR EVERY SHIPMENT
1. How were goods obtained by importer? By purchase or agreement to purchase ☐ By some means other than a purchase ☐ DO NOT INCLUDE PURCHASE AND NONPURCHASE GOODS IN SAME INVOICE. USE SEPARATE INVOICE FOR EACH
2. Place (city and country) and date obtained by importer London England 20th September 19763. Name of exporting carrier, Pan Am.4. Date of shipment
II. TO BE FILLED IN IF GOODS WERE PURCHASED OR AGREED TO BE PURCHASEDIII. TO BE FILLED IN IF GOODS WERE NOT PURCHASED
1. Name and address of seller Frames of Piccadilly, 169 Piccadilly, London W.1,1. Name and address of person from whom goods were obtained
2. Name and address of purchaser "Portsmouth Inc., 409 Fifth Avenue, New York NY 10017 U.S.A.2. Name and address of consignee
3. Date order accepted 29th September 19763. Name and address of person for whose account goods are shipped

V. THIS SECTION TO BE FILLED IN FOR EVERY SHIPMENT 1. IF GOODS WERE PURCHASED, have you stated in section IV, column 4, the purchase price of each item in the currency in which the goods were bought? option Yes: [x] option No: [ ] 2. IF THE GOODS WERE NOT PURCHASED, have you stated in section IV, column 4, the price that you would have received or would be willing to receive now if the goods were sold in the ordinary course of trade for exportation to the United States? option Yes: [x] option No: [ ] 3. What currency was used in this invoice transaction? paper 4. Whether the goods were purchased or obtained by the United States importer in some other manner, have you stated in section IV, column 6: (A) (1) The price at which you are now selling the goods or offering them for sale for home consumption, including all applicable taxes? option Yes: [x] option No: [ ] (2) Is this price freely offered to anyone who wishes to buy the goods for home consumption? option Yes: [ ] option No: [x] (B) (1) Have you stated in section IV, column 7, the price at which you are now selling the goods or offering them for sale for export to the United States and whether this price is f.o.b., c.i.f., c.&f., or whatever the fact may be? option Yes: [ ] option No: [x] (2) Is this price freely offered to anyone who wishes to buy the goods for export to the United States? option Yes: [x] option No: [ ] 5. Have you listed all charges and stated whether each amount has been included in or excluded from the invoice amount? option Yes: [ ] option No: [x] Is the inland freight included in the invoice price or value? option Yes: [ ] option No: [x] Is the price or value of the goods the same at the factory as at the point of delivery? option Yes: [ ] option No: [x] If the answer is No, have any sales been made at an ex-factory price? option Yes: [x] option No: [ ] 6. Are any rebates, drawbacks, bounties, or other grants allowed upon the exportation of the goods? option Yes: [ ] option No: [x] If so, have all been separately itemized? option Yes: [x] option No: [ ] 7. If such of similar goods are being sold or offered for sale in the home market for home consumption, what taxes are applicable and are they included in the price shown in section IV, column 6?
